.TH "GPUDEVICE.CREATESAMPLER" "3JS" "June 18, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
GPUDevice.createSampler \- GPUDevice: createSampler() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]createSampler()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]GPUDevice\f[R] interface creates a \f[CR]GPUSampler\f[R], which
controls how shaders transform and filter texture resource data.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
createSampler()
createSampler(descriptor)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]descriptor\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An object containing the following properties:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]addressModeU\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An enumerated value specifying the behavior of the sampler when the
sample footprint width extends beyond the width of the texture.
Possible values are:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqclamp\-to\-edge\(dq\f[R]: The texture coordinates are clamped
between 0.0 and 1.0, inclusive.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqrepeat\(dq\f[R]: The texture coordinates wrap to the other
side of the texture.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqmirror\-repeat\(dq\f[R]: The texture coordinates wrap to the
other side of the texture, but the texture is flipped when the integer
part of the coordinate is odd.
.PP
If omitted, \f[CR]addressModeU\f[R] defaults to
\f[CR]\(dqclamp\-to\-edge\(dq\f[R].
.RE
.TP
\f[B]addressModeV\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An enumerated value specifying the behavior of the sampler when the
sample footprint height extends beyond the height of the texture.
Possible and default values are the same as for \f[CR]addressModeU\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]addressModeW\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An enumerated value specifying the behavior of the sampler when the
sample footprint depth extends beyond the depth of the texture.
Possible and default values are the same as for \f[CR]addressModeU\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]compare\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
If specified, the sampler will be a comparison sampler of the specified
type.
Possible (enumerated) values are:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqnever\(dq\f[R]: Comparison tests never pass.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqless\(dq\f[R]: A provided value passes the comparison test if
it is less than the sampled value.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqequal\(dq\f[R]: A provided value passes the comparison test if
it is equal to the sampled value.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqless\-equal\(dq\f[R]: A provided value passes the comparison
test if it is less than or equal to the sampled value.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqgreater\(dq\f[R]: A provided value passes the comparison test
if it is greater than the sampled value.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqnot\-equal\(dq\f[R]: A provided value passes the comparison
test if it is not equal to the sampled value.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqgreater\-equal\(dq\f[R]: A provided value passes the
comparison test if it is greater than or equal to the sampled value.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqalways\(dq\f[R]: Comparison tests always pass.
.PP
Comparison samplers may use filtering, but the sampling results will be
implementation\-dependent and may differ from the normal filtering
rules.
.RE
.TP
\f[B]label\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A string providing a label that can be used to identify the object, for
example in \f[CR]GPUError\f[R] messages or console warnings.
.TP
\f[B]lodMinClamp\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A number specifying the minimum level of detail used internally when
sampling a texture.
If omitted, \f[CR]lodMinClamp\f[R] defaults to 0.
.TP
\f[B]lodMaxClamp\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A number specifying the maximum level of detail used internally when
sampling a texture.
If omitted, \f[CR]lodMaxClamp\f[R] defaults to 32.
.TP
\f[B]maxAnisotropy\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Specifies the maximum anisotropy value clamp used by the sampler.
If omitted, \f[CR]maxAnisotropy\f[R] defaults to 1.
.RS
.PP
Most implementations support \f[CR]maxAnisotropy\f[R] values in a range
between 1 and 16, inclusive.
The value used will be clamped to the maximum value that the underlying
platform supports.
.RE
.TP
\f[B]magFilter\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An enumerated value specifying the sampling behavior when the sample
footprint is smaller than or equal to one texel.
Possible values are:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqnearest\(dq\f[R]: Return the value of the texel nearest to the
texture coordinates.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]\(dqlinear\(dq\f[R]: Select two texels in each dimension and
return a linear interpolation between their values.
.PP
If omitted, \f[CR]magFilter\f[R] defaults to \f[CR]\(dqnearest\(dq\f[R].
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The \f[CR]float32\-filterable\f[R] feature needs to be
enabled for \f[CR]r32float\f[R]\-, \f[CR]rg32float\f[R]\-, and
\f[CR]rgba32float\f[R]\-\f[CR]format\f[R] \f[CR]GPUTexture\f[R]s to be
filterable.
.RE
.RE
.TP
\f[B]minFilter\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An enumerated value specifying the sampling behavior when the sample
footprint is larger than one texel.
Possible and default values are the same as for \f[CR]magFilter\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]mipmapFilter\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An enumerated value specifying the behavior when sampling between mipmap
levels.
Possible and default values are the same as for \f[CR]magFilter\f[R].
.RE
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]GPUSampler\f[R] object instance.
.SS Validation
The following criteria must be met when calling
\f[B]\f[CB]createSampler()\f[B]\f[R], otherwise a
\f[CR]GPUValidationError\f[R] is generated and an invalid
\f[CR]GPUSampler\f[R] object is returned:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]lodMinClamp\f[R] is equal to or more than 0.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]lodMaxClamp\f[R] is equal to or more than \f[CR]lodMinClamp\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]maxAnisotropy\f[R] is equal to or more than 1.
.IP \(bu 2
If \f[CR]maxAnisotropy\f[R] is more than 1, \f[CR]magFilter\f[R],
\f[CR]minFilter\f[R], and \f[CR]mipmapFilter\f[R] are
\f[CR]\(dqlinear\(dq\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
The following snippet creates a \f[CR]GPUSampler\f[R] that does
trilinear filtering and repeats texture coordinates:
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// \&...\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] sampler = device.createSampler({
  addressModeU: \(dqrepeat\(dq,
  addressModeV: \(dqrepeat\(dq,
  magFilter: \(dqlinear\(dq,
  minFilter: \(dqlinear\(dq,
  mipmapFilter: \(dqlinear\(dq,
});
.EE
.PP
The WebGPU samples \c
.UR https://webgpu.github.io/webgpu-samples/samples/shadowMapping/
Shadow Mapping sample
.UE \c
\ uses comparison samplers to sample from a depth texture to render
shadows.
